# CLI Module Rules

## Purpose
This module contains all command-line interface tools for the Axiomancer game:
- `display.ts` - Shared ASCII art, colors, formatting utilities
- `combat-sim.cli.ts` - Standalone combat simulator
- `library-editor.cli.ts` - Iterative questionnaire for adding skills/effects
- `game.cli.ts` - Main game loop with exploration and combat

## Conventions
- All CLI entry points use `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang
- Use inquirer.js for interactive prompts
- Use the shared `display.ts` utilities for consistent formatting
- ASCII art and color codes live in `display.ts`, not in individual tools
- CLI files are named `*.cli.ts` to distinguish from library code
- Each CLI tool should be independently runnable via npm scripts

## Style
- Keep display logic separate from game logic
- Use `delay()` for dramatic pauses in narrative moments
- Use `typewriter()` for story text
- Use `divider()` and `boxHeader()` for visual structure
- Color-code by type: red=Heart, yellow=Body, cyan=Mind
